text.tspan: From My Iniquity Wash Me Thoroughly
You would make known wisdom to me.
Purge my sin with hyssop, and I’ll be clean.
Let me hear gladness and joy,
Do hide Your face from all my sins,
O God, blot out all my iniquities.
Create in me a clean heart,
Do not cast me from Your presence,
And sustain me with a willing spirit.
A broken and a contrite heart;
For in sacrifice You do not delight.
O God, do good unto Zion;
